Preheat broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce. Halve, deseed, and cut
@long green pepper{1}(halved, deseeded, and cut into 1-inch pieces). Halve,
peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). In a #small bowl{},
combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}, @water{1%tablespoon},
and @salt{pinch}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium ovenproof pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and
cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Heat another drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high
heat. Add green pepper and onion. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Stir cooked beef, @tomato paste{3%tablespoon}, @beef stock concentrate{1}, 
@jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, and @water{1%cup} into pan with veggies. Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce heat to a simmer. Cook until rice is tender, about
~{15%minutes}. Uncover and remove from heat.

Evenly sprinkle @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} over beef and rice mixture. Broil
until melted, about ~{1%minute}.

Divide finished beef and rice mixture between plates. Drizzle with hot sauce
crema.